      "span_text": "Volumetric blood flow was calculated by Q = π * (d/2) 2 * v / 1.6 [pL/s], where 1.6 represents the Baker-Wayland factor [CITATION_2] to correct for the parabolic velocity profile in microvessels with diameters >20 μm."
